ES2022 added real private fields with `#`. Unlike the old `_name` convention, these actually enforce privacy:

```js
class Counter {
  #count = 0;  // truly private
  increment() { this.#count++; }
  get value()  { return this.#count; }
}
```

Previously private fields were just convention (`_count`). Now they're enforced.

